RPE Landscape for frugivores

Elena Quintero

#Read data
library(readr)
frug <- read_delim("all_frug.csv", ";", escape_double = FALSE, col_types = cols(plant_family = col_factor(levels = c()), species = col_factor(levels = c())),  trim_ws = TRUE)
names(frug)

This RPE has variability in the Y-axis (QTY component) - coming from QLY = specific energyPDM/FFRMfrug_capacity/fruits_visit. Cecropia pachystachia has a very high Quality component - because the fruit_visit are very low (like 0.003). Main problem: too many plant species, all together Other problem: SE error bar for Cecropia pachystachia QLY doesnt appear (out of y limit)

#RPE landscape with no variability in QTY (fruit energy)

Conclusions

  • Include variability in QLY component?
  • What to do for Cecropia pachystachya outlayer?
  • Better to include numbers in each point and create a legend for species.
  • Reduce lenght name of plant species
  • Reduce plant species selected
